Add tests that configure the mock IMAP client's connect() to reject, and verify: (1) channel.status becomes 'error', (2) the error is propagated with correct message and cause. Similarly test SMTP sendMail rejection after connect. Example:

it('should set error status when IMAP connect fails', async () => {
  const channel = new EmailChannel(config, {
    createImapClient: () => ({ ...createMockImapClient(), connect: vi.fn().mockRejectedValue(new Error('auth failed')) }),
    createSmtpTransport: () => createMockSmtpTransport(),
  })
  await expect(channel.connect()).rejects.toThrow('Email connect failed')
  expect(channel.status).toBe('error')
})

